The paper deals with a large-scale distributed learning paradigm, Federated Learning, which involves statistical and computational challenges in the presence of heterogeneous data distribution and Byzantine machines. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) and Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC) categories. Additionally, the paper proposes a statistical model and algorithm to address the challenges, indicating that it may also belong to the Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) category. The presence of Byzantine machines suggests that the paper may also belong to the Cryptography and Security (cs.CR) category. Finally, the use of statistical guarantees for an outlier-robust clustering algorithm suggests that the paper may also belong to the Systems and Control (cs.SY) category.
